Jaws equal, mouth terminal; posterior terminus of maxilla reaching vertical through anterior third of orbit. Premaxillary teeth in two rows, with midcentral cusp more developed than remaining cusps; outer teeth row with 4(6), 5*(44), or 6(1) tricuspid teeth; inner tooth row with 4(5), 5*(41) or 6(5) tri- to pentacuspid teeth. Maxillary with 1(5) or 2(2) uni- to tricuspid teeth; dentary with four large tetra- to pentacuspid teeth, followed by series of 7-10 small, unicuspid teeth (
Fig. 2
).
